.TH XIL\-GUI "1" "2026\-04\-19" "xil\-pipeline 0.1.7" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
xil\-gui \- launch the xil\-pipeline web dashboard (Gradio)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xil\-gui
[\-h] [\-\-port PORT] [\-\-host HOST] [\-\-share]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Opens a browser\-based Gradio dashboard that supplements the CLI with four tabs:
.TP
.B Episodes
Workspace overview \(em all detected episodes with parse/stems/DAW/master completion status.
.TP
.B Audio Preview
Browse and play stems for any episode directly in the browser. Stems can be filtered by type (dialogue, sfx, music, ambience). Labels are enriched from the parsed JSON when available.
.TP
.B Run Stage
Launch pipeline stages (parse, produce, assemble, daw, master) against a selected episode with live log streaming. Dry\-run is on by default.
.TP
.B Timeline
Embeds the interactive HTML timeline generated by
.B xil\-daw \-\-timeline\-html
in an iframe. Prompts for generation when absent.
.PP
Requires the optional
.B [gui]
extra:
.IP
pip install \(aqxil\-pipeline[gui]\(aq
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-port\fR \fI\,PORT\/\fR
Port to listen on (default: 7860)
.TP
\fB\-\-host\fR \fI\,HOST\/\fR
Host address to bind (default: 127.0.0.1)
.TP
\fB\-\-share\fR
Generate a public ngrok URL for partner access. The URL is open (no authentication) and valid for up to 72 hours. Suitable for trusted collaborator sessions only.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Open locally:
.B xil\-gui
.TP
Custom port:
.B xil\-gui \-\-port 8080
.TP
Share with collaborators (generates public URL):
.B xil\-gui \-\-share
.TP
Via unified dispatcher:
.B xil gui
.SH NOTES
The dashboard detects episodes by globbing
.B cast_*.json
files in the current working directory. Run from the project workspace root.
.PP
Audio files are served from the workspace via Gradio's
.B allowed_paths
mechanism. The
.B \-\-share
tunnel streams audio through the ngrok relay.
.PP
Each Run Stage execution is an isolated subprocess. The dashboard remains responsive if a stage errors or is cancelled.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR xil (1),
.BR xil\-assemble (1),
.BR xil\-daw (1),
.BR xil\-produce (1)
